  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening public policy-making in Member States, based on scientific evidence, humanities-based knowledge, ethics and human rights frameworks (or Ensuring Responsive, Inclusive, Participatory and Representative Decision-Making) In West-Africa Sahel</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Following the AHC and WHC (Bamako-Liege 2017), the AYF (Banjul 2019), the sector is called to support the conceptualization and production of locally grounded theories and new knowledge on emerging trends to ensure the relevance of the SHS in achieving the 2030 and 2063 agendas and to consolidate the leadership of UNESCO in contemporary debates. The activity will tackle the crisis of African knowledge. Member States and relevant stakeholders will be assisted to improve multidisciplinary policymaking through a strengthened research-policy interface, informed by SHS research on sound policies on ethical issues in STI, AI and pertinent knowledge to the global sport and anti-doping agenda, GHA and intercultural dialogue. It will be based on GEWE, HRBA and active participation of youth and MDP.</narrative>
  </description>
